You might say that, but it's funny.  As much as I love crosswords, I don't find Scrabble that much fun.  Completed Scrabble boards don't look much like the puzzles we do, and to be good at it, you need a different skill set, one which includes learning the Scrabble dictionary.

And there are no clues involved, which is a major part of actual crosswords.

@Lenny

I've never heard of that game before, but, as I said to Sharon, just because a game has elements of a crossword doesn't mean it plays like one, or is attractive to avid crossword solvers.

On the other hand, if Lucy endorsed it...

