You can't know the cow anymore. Ground beef today is made from many different cows, which is one of the reasons it needs to be well-cooked.

Sweetbreads used to be one of the courses served at every Goodbye, Columbus-type wedding or Bar Mitzvah I attended when I was a child. Couldn't bring myself to try them. I thought they were brains, but later learned they were the cow's thymus gland. Yuk. Anyway, organ meat is pretty unhealthy if you have a cholesterol problem.

@Helen Wright
