@Cherry
My mother (bless her memory) used to love "pchai" - a disgusting production of spiced ground meat encased in calf's foot jelly. Even more repellent than it sounds, and the smell it produced as the foot boiled for hours....

We used to call it salami jello. Had we been told, "Eat pchai or die!" we'd have given both possibilities serious consideration.

