@Helen Wright
Whenever anyone talks about eating tongue it reminds me of a restaurant near our apartment when we lived in St. Peterburg Russia.  (Not Florida....)

St. Petersburg is a very tourist-y city, so many restaurants have English language menus, if you ask.  One of the dishes on this menu was "beef language."  We puzzled for a minute and then said, "Tongue!"  In English we can often use the words interchangeably.  In Russian they are the same word.

